THEORETICAL FOUNDATION (implement these in order):

STEP 1 — Importance Weighter (file: meld/core/weighter.py)
The bias introduced by training only on new data is:
  bias = E_{p_new}[loss] - E_{p_full}[loss]
Fix this with importance weighting:
  w(x) = p_full(f(x)) / p_new(f(x))
where f(x) is the backbone embedding. Estimate this ratio using the stored
per-class Gaussian statistics (class_means, class_covs from TaskSnapshot).
Weights get multiplied into the per-sample CE loss inside GeometryConstrainedUpdater.
Clip weights to [0.05, 20.0] and normalise to mean=1.

STEP 2 — PAC Equivalence Bound (file: meld/core/oracle.py, add method)
After importance weighting is applied, derive:
  ε(n, δ) = sqrt(Var(w)/n)              [IW estimation error, Cortes 2010]
           + λ_max(F) * ||θ_delta-θ_old||  [curvature term, Kirkpatrick 2017]
           + sqrt(log(1/δ) / 2n)        [PAC concentration, Hoeffding]
This bound means: with probability ≥ 1−δ, the accuracy gap between the delta-trained
model and the full-retrained model is at most ε.
Key: this bound is only valid if importance weighting is applied (Step 1 first).

STEP 3 — MMD Input-Space Drift Detector (file: meld/core/drift.py, add class)
The existing KLManifoldDriftDetector runs AFTER training. We also need a PRE-training
detector that measures whether the new batch looks like an out-of-distribution sample.
Use Maximum Mean Discrepancy (MMD) on embedding statistics vs stored Gaussian params.
If MMD exceeds threshold, flag as potential covariate shift before training starts.

STEP 4 — Wire Avalanche Baselines (file: meld/benchmarks/avalanche_baselines.py)
Currently returns "pending_implementation". Wire EWC, LwF, and DER++ from
avalanche-lib using the same backbone (resnet32) and same task split as BenchmarkRunner.
Output the same JSON schema {top1, ece, forgetting, wall_time_seconds} so results
are directly comparable.

EVALUATION METRICS (what to report):
- Equivalence gap: cosine similarity between delta and full-retrain confusion matrices
- Compute savings: (full_retrain_time - delta_time) / full_retrain_time * 100
- Forgetting: drop in old-task accuracy after new tasks are learned
- ECE (Expected Calibration Error): calibration vs full retrain
- PAC bound value: the computed ε for δ=0.05 at each task

DATASETS: CIFAR-10 (5 tasks × 2 classes) and CIFAR-100 (10 tasks × 10 classes)
